title: Q7 Physical Science HiSET.S.1.2
prompt: Two vehicles begin traveling at the same time. Vehicle A travels at 45 miles per hour (MPH) for two hours. Vehicle B travels at 80 MPH for one hour. Which vehicle travels the farthest, and how much farther does it travel?
feedback: Using the distance formula and your understanding of distance, rate of travel, and time, Vehicle A has a rate of 45 MPH multiplied by a time of two hours, equaling to a distance of 90 miles. Vehicle B has a rate of 80 miles per hour multiplied by a time of one hour, equaling 80 miles. Vehicle A traveled 10 miles farther than Vehicle B.
